column63: For "was_close", I arbitraily decide how close a race was, typically based on finish time.
The values used are as following
1: Extremely close (anyone can reasonably win within the last few minutes of the race)
.75: Racers are "somewhat" close, usually denoted by both racers simultaneously being on the same level, but with one further ahead.
.5: When I have no idea how close it was
.25: Not that close but sorta (Racers are within ~10 minutes of each other at the end, assuming an ~8 hour game.)
0: One racer finished far ahead of the other. There will be little question as to who will win well before the end.
